article.headline: VMI 78, Navy 73
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Levar Joseph scored 18 points as Virginia Military Institute beat Navy 78-73 on Sunday -- the Keydets first-ever win over the Midshipmen. Joseph and Matt Coward each sank a pair of free throws in the final 14 seconds to protect the Keydets' slim lead and help break a 21-game Navy winning streak in the series. Coward had 16 points and converted 12 of 14 free throws for the Keydets (2-0). Reggie Williams added 14 points. Navy (2-2) led 58-50 with 10:02 to play, but the Keydets outscored the Mids 21-5 over the next eight minutes to lead 71-63 with 1:53 to play. Matt Fannin recorded his first career double-double and led Navy with career-highs of 20 points and 13 rebounds. Taj Mathews also posted a career-high with 19 points. Laramie Mergerson scored 10 points for the Mids but left with an injury with 14 minutes to play and never returned. The Mids made just 3 of 26 three-pointers and shot just 38 percent for the game. Navy was up 35-34 at the half. The game was tied at 47 before the Mids went on a 9-1 run for a 56-48 lead early in the second half.
